    <fr:title text="Preserving covers from a dcpo presentation">Preserving covers from a <fr:link href="/jms-00A9/" title="Dcpo presentation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00A9/" display-uri="jms-00A9" type="local">dcpo presentation</fr:link></fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="source">Definition 2.2, <fr:link href="/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" title="Presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" display-uri="jung-moshier-vickers-2008" type="local">[jung-moshier-vickers-2008]</fr:link></fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (P,C\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/jms-00A9/" title="Dcpo presentation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00A9/" display-uri="jms-00A9" type="local">dcpo presentation</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a dcpo; a monotone map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{P}\xrightarrow {{f}}{D}]]></fr:tex> is said to <html:em>preserve covers in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex></html:em> when for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\lhd _C U]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[fa \sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup _{x\in  U} fx]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
