            <fr:title text="The free dcpo on a dcpo presentation">The free dcpo on a <fr:link href="/jms-00A9/" title="Dcpo presentation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00A9/" display-uri="jms-00A9" type="local">dcpo presentation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Definition 2.3, <fr:link href="/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" title="Presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" display-uri="jung-moshier-vickers-2008" type="local">[jung-moshier-vickers-2008]</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (P,C\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/jms-00A9/" title="Dcpo presentation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00A9/" display-uri="jms-00A9" type="local">dcpo presentation</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {P}]]></fr:tex> be a dcpo. A morphism of preorders <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{P}\xrightarrow {{\eta }}{\bar {P}}]]></fr:tex> is said to exhibit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {P}]]></fr:tex> as the <html:em>free dcpo generated by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (P,C\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex></html:em> if the following conditions hold:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{P}\xrightarrow {{\eta }}{\bar {P}}]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="/jms-00A8/" title="Preserving covers from a dcpo presentation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00A8/" display-uri="jms-00A8" type="local">preserves covers</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every cover preserving map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{P}\xrightarrow {{f}}{A}]]></fr:tex> into a dcpo <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> factors through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{P}\xrightarrow {{\eta }}{\bar {P}}]]></fr:tex> by a unique continuous map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\bar {P}}\xrightarrow {{\bar {f}}}{D}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
