            <fr:title text="Dcpo presentation">Dcpo presentation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Definition 2.1, <fr:link href="/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" title="Presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" display-uri="jung-moshier-vickers-2008" type="local">[jung-moshier-vickers-2008]</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em>dcpo presentation</html:em> consists of a preorder <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> of generators together with a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C\subseteq  P\times \Omega ^{{\mathopen {}\left \lvert P\right \rvert \mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> such that for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (a\lhd  U\right )\mathclose {}}\in  C]]></fr:tex>, the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is directed in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>. Absent the condition that every distinguished subset be directed, we refer to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> as a <html:em>cover set</html:em> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
